    <h3>DEFINITIONS AND NOTATION</h3>
    <div class="texto-entrada">
        <h1>What is one ED?</h1>
    </div>
    <p class="fw-mio2">
        Is the that permit me find the velocity on a exact point or too we can say, the derivative is the that permit me find the line tangent a  given function.
    </p>    
    <p class="fw-mio2">
        y = y(x) and its derivatives y, y 0, y 00, ..., y n) is called a differential equation.
    </p>
    <p class="fw-mio2"> \[ F(x, y, y'*y'', ..., y^n)=0 \] </p>
    <p class="fw-mio2">
        \[ F(x, y, \frac{dy}{dx'}, \frac{d^2y}{dx^2}, ... , \frac{d^ny}{dx^n})=0 \]
    </p>
    <p class="fw-mio2">              
        \[ y^n=f(x,y,y`.y``,…,y^n-1) \]
    </p>
    <p class="fw-mio2">
        Examples of Differential Equations:
