            <p class="fw-mio2">
                • CLASSIFICATION:Differential equations are classified according to their type, order, and linearity and degree:
            </p>
            <p class="fw-mio2">
                <b>1)</b> Type:
                </br>
                ㅤㅤㅤ<b>a)</b> Ordinary differential equations: these equations contain only ordinary derivatives with respect to a single independent variable.
                <br/>
                ㅤㅤㅤ<b>b)</b> Equations in partial derivatives: they contain partial derivatives with respect to two or more independent variables.
            </p>

            <p class="fw-mio2">
                <b>2)</b> Order: Upper derivative involved in the equation.
            </p>                         
            
            <p class="fw-mio2">
                <b>3)</b> Linearity:
                </br>
                ㅤㅤㅤ<b>a)</b> The dependent variable and its derivatives are of 1st degree.
                <br/>
                ㅤㅤㅤ<b>b)</b> The coefficients only depend on the independent variable.
            </p>
            
            <p class="fw-mio2">
                <b>4)</b> Degree: It is the exponent of the highest derivative.                
