            <h1>Examples</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="fw-mio2">
            SOLUTIONS OF D.E.: The solution (or integral) of the differential equation is any function y = y(x) that, introduced in the differential equation, transforms it into equality.
        </p>
        <p class="fw-mio2">
            <b>1)</b> Types of solutions:
            <br/>
            ㅤㅤㅤ<b>a)</b> Explicit: The dependent variable y is expressed only in terms of the independent variable x and constants.
            <br/>
            ㅤㅤㅤ<b>b)</b> Implicit: This is a relation G (x, y) = 0 in which y cannot be solved using elementary functions. All y(x) satisfying G(x, y) = 0 are solutions.
        </p>         
        
        <p class="fw-mio2">
            The n-parametric family G (x, y, C1, C2, · · ·, Cn) = 0 is the general solution of a differential equation of order n if every solution of that equation can be obtained from that family.
        </p>
